Software Design Document (SDD)

Project: CineChat: An Smart multimodal video chatbot
1. Introduction
1.1 Purpose
This document describes the design of ‘CineChat: An smart multimodal video chatbot’ that allows users to interact with video content through chatbot. The system uses advanced AI techniques such as Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG), OCR, speech-to-text, and vision-language models.
1.2 Scope
The system enables:
    • Video ingestion (YouTube/local upload) 
    • Frame and audio extraction 
    • Speech-to-text conversion 
    • OCR-based text extraction from frames 
    • Multimodal indexing and retrieval 
    • Conversational question answering 
    • Visual + textual response generation
    • Evaluation of retrieval and generation performance 
1.3 Goals
Goal of the project is it understand the context of the video by extracting video, image, audio and text from it using the timeframe and answering the user query by making use of vectordb and RAG.


