3. System Modules

3.1 Video Ingestion Module
CiniChat shall accept the YouTube URL or local file, download the video and extract metadata.
Anchor: SDD_3_1

3.2 Frame Extraction Module
System shall extract frames, assign timestamps to each frame and store images for indexing.
Anchor: SDD_3_2

3.3 Audio Extraction Module
System shall extracts audio from video and store it in wav format.
Anchor: SDD_3_3

3.4 Speech-to-Text Module
System shall convert audio into transcript and generate timestamped text segments.
Anchor: SDD_3_4 

3.5 OCR Module
System shall extracts text from video frames and captures slides, code snippets and UI text.
Anchor: SDD_3_5 

3.6 Multimodal Dataset Builder
System shall combine transcript, OCR text, frames, timestamps and metadata. 
Anchor: SDD_3_6

3.7 Embedding Generation Module
System shall converts text and images into embeddings. 
Anchor: SDD_3_7

3.8 Vector Database Module
System shall stores embeddings in LanceDB using separate collections: 
        ? text_collection 
        ? image_collection 
Anchor: SDD_3_8

3.9 Retrieval Module
System shall perform hybrid search (semantic + keyword search)
    • Retrieves: 
        ? relevant text chunks 
        ? relevant images 
    • Returns top-k results 
Anchor: SDD_3_9

3.10 Conversational AI Module
System shall make use of  LLM (Groq / LLaMA / LLaVA) , maintain conversation memory and provide context-aware responses. 
Anchor: SDD_3_10

3.11 Vision-Language Module
System shall processes images  and text together by making use of  LLaVA model thus generating multimodal reasoning-based answers. 
Anchor: SDD_3_11

3.12 Streamlit UI Module
System shall use interactive chat interface for following
    • Video upload / URL input 
    • Displays: 
        ? answers 
        ? retrieved frames 
        ? chat history 
        ? timestamps 
Anchor: SDD_3_12

3.13 Evaluation Module (NEW)
System shall be evaluated to measure the quality of:
    • retrieval system 
    • generated answers 
    • multimodal grounding accuracy 
Anchor: SDD_3_13

3.14 Key Evaluation Metrics
System shall use following evalution metrics to check the performance
1. Retrieval Evaluation
Measures how well relevant content is retrieved.
    • Precision@K 
    • Recall@K 
    • Mean Reciprocal Rank (MRR) 
2. Generation Evaluation
Evaluates LLM response quality.
    • Faithfulness (is answer supported by context?) 
    • Relevance (does it answer the question?) 
    • Coherence (is response logically structured?) 
Tools:
    • RAGAS framework 
3. Multimodal Evaluation
Checks correctness of:
    • image relevance 
    • OCR correctness 
    • frame alignment with query 
4. Hallucination Detection
Ensures model does not generate unsupported facts.
    • Compare response with retrieved context 
    • Penalize unsupported claims 
Anchor: SDD_3_14
Evaluation Workflow
User Query
     ?
Retrieval Output (Text + Images)
     ?
LLM Generated Answer
     ?
Compare with Ground Truth / Context
     ?
Compute Metrics
     ?
Store Evaluation Score
3.15 Output of Evaluation Module
System shall have following reports
    • Score dashboard 
    • Retrieval accuracy report 
    • Answer quality score 
    • Error analysis logs 
Anchor: SDD_3_15
